To fix the "misarranged" layout on tablet devices (specifically the awkward transitions between mobile and full desktop layouts), I will refine the responsive breakpoints.

**Key Fixes:**
1.  **Navigation Rail (App.tsx):** I will lock the layout spacer to a fixed width (`w-[80px]`) regardless of expansion. The expanded sidebar will now strictly **overlay** the content rather than pushing it, preventing jarring layout shifts on tablets.
2.  **Profile Header (Profile.tsx):** I will change the "Founder ID" card layout to remain **stacked** on tablets (`md`) and only switch to horizontal row on larger desktops (`lg`). This prevents the avatar and bio from getting squashed side-by-side on 768px screens.
3.  **Layout Padding:** Adjusted container padding to better suit tablet viewports.

